21 of my favorite entrepreneurship quotes  

Words of wisdom that will completely change your business thinking. 

// Thread //

If your business can’t operate without you being there;

You don’t have a business.. 

You have a JOB.

Steve Jobs famously once said;

‘Don’t let the noise of others’ opinions drown out your own inner voice.’

Be careful who you take advice from.

After 8 companies and 15 years in entrepreneurship;

Here’s 11 of my most important business lessons for you. 

// Thread //

I quit my last ever job 16 years ago.

How I did it and how you can do the same.

// Thread //

Elon Musk famously once said;

‘When something is important enough, you do it even if the odds are not in your favor.’

Stop looking for a reason to quit, start looking for a reason to win.

If you have a business that can’t operate without you being there;

It’s not a business

It’s a job.

My millionaire mentor once said to me;

‘Focus on building your network. It will open more doors than your degree ever will.’

He was right.

Elon Musk famously once said;

‘When something is important enough, you do it even if the odds are not in your favor.’

Find your why, find your motivation.

If you get angry at random people on the internet;

You probably need to get some fresh air. 

And off your phone.

Steve Jobs famously once said;

‘Your time is limited, so don’t waste it living someone else’s life’

Who’s life are you living?

Steve Job’s famously once said;

‘It’s Innovation that distinguishes between a leader and a follower.’

Innovate, don’t procrastinate.

Key to success;

1. Make a plan
2. Stick to it

If your business stops when you’re not there;

You don’t have a business,

You have a job.

Elon Musk famously once said;

‘When something is important enough, you do it even if the odds are not in your favor.’

Find your why, and you’ll never lack motivation.
